x\in A\setminus B\implies x\in A\;\;\text{and}\;\;x\notin B
x\in A\cap B^c\implies x\in A\;\;\text{and}\;\;x\notin B
\begin{align} x\in A- B &\iff x \in A \land x\notin B \iff x \in A \land x\in B^c \iff x \in A\cap B^c\end{align}
\therefore A-B = A\cap B^c
